However, finding a Full House (by drawing one more Queen or Seven) would drastically increase the score to over 1000 points ((40 base + ~44 card chips) * (4 base + 8 joker mult) = 84 * 12 = 1008). Winning in 1 hand instead of 2 nets an extra $1 for the remaining hand and ensures I reach the next interest threshold, effectively gaining $2. Since I hold the Two Pair safely, there is no risk in using my discards to try to hit the Full House outs (2 Queens, 2 Sevens remaining). I will discard the four unrelated cards to maximize my chances.

